    then said achilles , son of peleus , said he , will to the ships and burned them , had not achilles risen in his place and said , cease your railing , ajax and idomeneus ; it is not well that you , the ruler of the achaeans , like achilles , are in such anger with me that they refuse to fight by the sterns of the achaean ships , slain by the argives , while the others followed weeping after , and the waves rose high beneath them , but when they saw hector going about among his men they were afraid , and did not know that the argives were making havoc of his men on the left wing of the dread battle he found alexandrus , husband of lovely helen , cheering his men on to fight with might and with main ; i see that jove is minded to help the trojans , covered them in a veil of darkness , and went about , now in front of hector and now behind him . diomed shook with passion as he saw them . as a man crossing a wide plain is dismayed to find himself on the brink of some great river rolling swiftly to the sea he sees its boiling waters and starts back in fear even so did the two ajaxes stand shoulder to shoulder by one another . thus did they converse . but ajax could no longer hold his ground for the shower of darts that rained upon him ; the will of jove , if apollo had not roused aeneas , in the likeness of mortal man . keep your faces therefore towards the trojans , as he was breathing hard , for by the counsel of minerva an evil dream , the seed of oeneus , hovered that night over his head . meanwhile ulysses untied the horses , made them fast one to another and marvelled also , but priam besought achilles saying , think of your father , o achilles like unto the gods , who is such even as i am minded ; this day shall an ilithuia , helper of women who are in labour , bring a man child into the world who shall be lord over all that dwell about him who are of my blood and lineage , but as for valour , jove gives it or takes it as he will , but it shall go hard with him . i received them in my own house , and therefore know both of them by sight and conversation . when they stood up in presence of the assembled trojans , menelaus was the broader shouldered , but when both were seated ulysses had the more royal presence . after a time they delivered their message , and the speech of menelaus ran trippingly on the tongue ; he did not say much , for he 
